<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="951" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1599.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-05"><hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In regard to the <hi rend="italic">Eureka</hi> telegraph to the <hi rend="italic">York town</hi> at San Juan del Sur the information
                            sent the department June 2. Repeat to American legation at San Salvador
                            the other information in your telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>